detailedDescription.articleBody: Dr.-Ing. h.c. F. Porsche AG, usually shortened to Porsche AG, is a German automobile manufacturer specializing in high-performance sports cars, SUVs and sedans.

detailedDescription.articleBody: The Adecco Group, based in Zurich, Switzerland, is the world's second largest Human Resources provider and temporary staffing firm, and a Fortune Global 500 company.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Continental AG, commonly known as Continental, is a German multinational automotive parts manufacturing company specializing in brake systems, interior electronics, automotive safety, powertrain and chassis components, tachographs, tires and other parts for the automotive and transportation industries.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Robert Bosch GmbH, or Bosch, is a German multinational engineering and technology company headquartered in Gerlingen, near Stuttgart, Germany. The company was founded by Robert Bosch in Stuttgart in 1886. Bosch is 92% owned by Robert Bosch Stiftung, a charitable institution.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: रॉबर्ट बॉश जीएमबीएच, या बॉश, एक जर्मन बहुराष्ट्रीय इंजीनियरिंग और प्रौद्योगिकी कंपनी है, जिसका मुख्यालय जर्मनी के स्टटगार्ट के पास गेरलिंगन में है। कंपनी की स्थापना रॉबर्ट बॉश ने 1886 में स्टटगार्ट में की थी, बॉश 92 वर्षीय रॉबर्ट बॉश स्टिफ्टंग, एक धर्मार्थ संस्था, के स्वामित्व में है।

detailedDescription.articleBody: Tata Motors Limited, formerly Tata Engineering and Locomotive Company, is an Indian multinational automotive manufacturing company headquartered in Mumbai, Maharashtra, India. It is a part of Tata Group, an Indian conglomerate.
